  "success_stories": "INCIDENT #1\nRaven Alert: Multiple Gunshot Alert on 05/12/25 at 06:16PM at 2500 blk Sonoma Blvd.\nDispatch CFS:\n25-4619: 05/12/25 at 06:17PM Raven alerted to multiple gunshots heard in the area of 2500 blk Sonoma Blvd. A\nvictim called and stated that a subject had shot at his vehicle, and he had been struck once in the stomach. One adult\nvictim was located with non-life-threatening injuries.\nOriginal CFS was in the area of Broadway/ Tennessee St.\nActual scene and RAVEN gunshot alert was in the 2500 blk of Sonoma Blvd.\n\nINCIDENT #2\nRaven Alert: Multiple gunshots alert on 10/06/24 at 1:35AM close to 500blk Capitol St.\nDispatch CFS:\n24-10161: 10/06/24 \u0013 1:36AM/ Corner of Capitol St. & Marin St.\nVictim was shot and unable to call 911 prior to being found by officers. Suspect contacted and arrested with firearm recovered\n\nINCIDENT #3\nVPD Officers were dispatched to the area of Florida St. and Mare Island Way after receiving a notification from CHP about a wanted felony vehicle. This suspect vehicle fled from Folsom PD earlier in the day and led officers on a county wide pursuit making threats to commit suicide by cop. According to CHP and info per Flock, the vehicle was now in this area of Vallejo. A VPD officer conducted a Flock ALPR search and was able to find a specific area of where the suspect vehicle was last seen. During their area check, Officers located the vehicle and were able to take the suspect into custody without incident.",
